28/01/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Independent Trade Union of Defence Workers met on Tuesday (27 January) with Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski to discuss their demand for a 30 per cent pay raise.
Although the two sides failed to find a solution, they agreed to meet again next week.
The union threatened to go on strike as of 7 February.
In other news Tuesday, Justice Minister Ixhet Memeti signed a request seeking the extradition of Xhemail Hiseni, former commander of the National Liberation Army.
UNMIK is holding him in Kosovo.
Also Tuesday, a Council of Europe committee issued a report recommending reforms in Macedonia's media.
Citing bias and links to political or business interests, the report concluded the level of journalism is unsatisfactory.
(MIA, A1 TV - 27/01/04)
